    \item The t test statistic is \Sexpr{formatC(m.t$statistic,format="f",digits=4)} with \Sexpr{formatC(m.t$parameter,format="f",digits=0)} df \tabrefp{tab:mussels2}.
    \item The p-value is \Sexpr{swvPvalue(m.t$p.value)} \tabrefp{tab:mussels2}.
    \item The $H_{0}$ is not rejected because the $p-value > \alpha$.
    \item The methyl mercury levels do not appear to be different in mussels from the impacted and reference sites.
  \end{Enumerate}

