\section*{Notes From Professor}
\begin{itemize}
  \item If you do not use informative subscripts, then make sure that you explicitly define what the ``1'' and ``2'' subscripts mean.
  \item Make sure that you provide evidence for the fact that the two groups are independent.
  \item Note in 11.25 that the sample size is so small that the assumption is that the sample distributions must be normal; ``not strongly skewed'' is not adequate with this small sample size.
  \item Note that in 11.25, it is easier to create a tab-delimited text file to load the data.
  \item Note that in 11.25, if you decide to use \R{Summarize()} to get the sample means then do NOT set \R{digits=1} because this rounds the means to too few significant digits.  In other words, make sure to take note of the scale that the measurements were made on when rounding.  Note that \R{digits=3} would be more appropriate. 
\end{itemize}

